        <type>bool</type>
        <definition>bool faiss::InvertedListsIterator::has_search_callbacks_</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>has_search_callbacks_</name>
        <qualifiedname>faiss::InvertedListsIterator::has_search_callbacks_</qualifiedname>
        <initializer>= false</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>When true, iterate_codes will invoke <ref refid="structfaiss_1_1InvertedListsIterator_1a6b2266aa705566b234a26fa9a6019fb3" kindref="member">on_distance_computed()</ref> and <ref refid="structfaiss_1_1InvertedListsIterator_1ab0d9f6b16cd02b54554690e040ecf5b5" kindref="member">on_heap_changed()</ref> via virtual dispatch. When false (the default), iterate_codes skips the callbacks entirely — the guard branch is perfectly predicted and costs ~0 cycles, so non-callback users pay no overhead. Derived classes that override the callbacks should set this to true in their constructor. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
